args:
Mei Hou Wang's hostility to mortals leaves
Xuan Zang no choice but to try and seal him,
which saddens Wu Kong greatly. Zhu Bajie
then tells him about living without regret,
which causes the boy to redouble his efforts
to change the situation.
No... I am not yet finished...
He clearly has no intention\nof surrendering quietly.
And he ain't pullin' any punches, eitherâ€”\nhe really wants to see us dead!
Uh, master? Why are you pickin' up\nthe Jin Gu Er there?
Though damaged, it can still be used.
You're gonna seal him in it!
Forgive me, Wu Kong. It must be done.
O power universal. Crown of heaven!\nTake form thy halo and see evil bound!
I know this relic... It is that hateful piece\nof trash that entrapped me before!
This is UNFORGIVABLE! You mortals are\nnaught but skittering, selfish insects!
Yes. Mei Hou Wang has been sealed\ninside the Jin Gu Er.
I will apply a more powerful seal and\nreturn it safely to the cave once more.
Remember your duty, Wu Kong.\nRemember the path you have chosen.
No matter what may come,\nyou must see your duty done.
...Mmm. It took some time to mend the\nbroken Jin Gu Er, but the seal is now\ncomplete once more.
Then it seems this adventure is overâ€”\nthough I wish we had seen it through\nto a more pleasant conclusion.
You gonna try and comfort him?
No. I have no right to do so.
I have taken his friend from him.
And if it leads to his hating me...\nWell, what's done is done.
Hey there, Wu Kong! Can't remember the\nlast time I saw you lookin' this low.
Just wondering if you hate her now.
I'm the one who was wrong.
No, it's not that. I mean, Mei Hou Wang\nfrom before actually WAS a decent guy.
My actions are what was wrong.
Mei Hou Wang transformed because\nI broke the Jin Gu Er.
But I'm also wrong because of\nwhat I thought.
The moment Mei Hou Wang attacked us,\nI saw how dangerous he was and realized\nthat maybe he SHOULD be sealed away.
I'm a crappy sealer AND a crappy friend,\nand I don't have the right to be mad at\nanybody but myself.
I just have to accept whatever happens\nand...I dunno. Move on, I guess.

*sigh* If I had a gold piece for every time
the two of you threw up your hands and
said you just had to accept somethin',
I could buy some sense for both of you!
Listen, kiddo. You keep talkin' about how\nall of this is inevitable, but it ain't.
I mean, take Sha Wujing over there.
I will thank you to leave me out of your\nhypotheticals while I'm trying to discern\nthe deepest secrets of the Jin Gu Er.
As you know, Sha Wujing is...\nWell, he's a very specific guy.
But what you may not know is that back\nwhen I was commanding an army in Taiwu,\nhe sold us out and defected.
And then he took those damned weapons\nhe loves so much and tried to kill me\nwith 'em. ...Lots of times, actually.

Hee hee! Which weapons are we talking
about here? The bone tank? Perhaps the
obstruction armament? Oh, but I DID do
some of my finest work during that time!

Even though the two of us had once been
on the same side and known each other
for a good stretch, this guy didn't give one
lick about the horrors he put me through.
If one is not prepared to be hated,\nthen one should select a career\nother than weapon development.

Weapons are the ruler by which the power
of a civilization is measured. I lived on the
cutting edge of tech and had responsibility
for all of Taiwu thrust upon me!
Compared with the progress of culture and\ncivilization, what happens to Zhu Bajie is\na trifling matter, is it not?
*sigh* The heavens only know why I'm\ndoomed to be shackled to this guy...
But look, Wu Kongâ€”this ain't the time\nto throw up your hands and talk about\nhow there's nothin' you can do.
You only get to do that once you know\nyou've tried absolutely everything and are\nsure you can move on without regret.
Without regret...? Huh. So maybe there\nstill ARE some things I can do...
See, that's exactly what I'm sayin'.\nOh, and while we're at it, the same\npiece of advice applies to Xuan Zang.
If she's got time to blame herself,\nshe's got time to get out there and\ntry something else.

And if you make a big ol' mess of things,
THAT'S when you can let out a sigh and
say you're powerless. ...Least that's what
the wife says, anyway.
So how 'bout it? You feeling pumped?\nReady to give it another go?
Yeah, I am! I still have things to say to\nboth Xuan Zang AND Mei Hou Wang!
So first, I'm gonna try talking to\nmy master one more time!
It is rare indeed to see a man who insists\non forcing his own way all the time\nattempt to build bridges between others.
I ain't building bridgesâ€”I'm just\ndoing what's right.

I suppose something needed to be done.
If Wu Kong had stayed in that state, Master
Xuan Zang would remain depressed, and
Mei Hou Wang's fate would be sealed.
Exactly. Anyway, did you hear Wu Kong\nsay he wanted to talk with Mei Hou Wang?
Mei Hou Wang saved me, so I owe him.\nGuess it's time to start payin' it back.
I assume you have a plan, hmmMMM?
Yep. Mei Hou Wang woke up when he\nabsorbed the evil power that came outta\nthe Jin Gu Er, yeah?

So we just gotta give him and his fiend
buddies the beatdown and purge that
dark power he's got. That oughta give
Wu Kong enough time to chat him up.
An even sloppier strategy than I first\nanticipated! Oh, but you DO never fail\nto impress, old friend.
I take it you're out, then?
Oh, I am most definitely ï¼‚in.ï¼‚ Sadly,\nthis is likely to be my last chance at\nunraveling the secrets of the Jin Gu Er.
Hey, whatever gets you through the\nday. Now let's roll!
